    "body" : "<p>You can always write it like this </p>\n\n<pre><code>String[] errorSoon = {\"Hello\",\"World\"};\n\nFor (int x=0;x&lt;errorSoon.length;x++) // in this way u create a for     loop that would like display the elements which are inside the array     errorSoon.oh errorSoon.length is the same as errorSoon&lt;2 \n\n{\n   System.out.println(\" \"+errorSoon[x]); // this will output those two     words, at the top hello and world at the bottom of hello.  \n}\n</code></pre>\n"
